In [[Tenmei]] 5 (1785), [[Matsumae Domain]] trader and agent {{ill|Murayama Denbee|ja|村山伝兵衛}} (1738–1813) is said to have founded the small shrine of {{nihongo|Sōya Daijingū|宗谷大神宮}}, enshrining [[Amaterasu]] as guardian of the north gate.<ref name="Jinjacho">{{cite web |url=https://hokkaidojinjacho.jp/北門神社/ |script-title=ja:北門神社 |trans-title=Hokumon Jinja |language=Japanese |publisher=Hokkaidō Jinja-chō |accessdate=28 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.city.wakkanai.hokkaido.jp/gaiyo/ayumi.html |script-title=ja:稚内のあゆみ（歴史）|trans-title=History of Wakkanai |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Wakkanai, Hokkaido|Wakkanai City]] |accessdate=28 September 2019}}</ref> In 1896 the shrine was transferred to its current location and renamed [[Hokumon Shrine|Hokumon Jinja]], with [[Takemikazuchi]] and [[Kotoshironushi]] enshrined alongside Amaterasu.<ref name="Jinjacho"/>

