The area known as '''Fujinosawa''' in {{ill|Minami-ku, Sapporo|ja|南区 (札幌市)|12=draft}} was once a logging site operated by the Murayama family. The name "Marujugo" persisted locally due to the branded marks on timber. Although the place name faded after the construction of {{ill|Fujinosawa Station|ja|藤の沢駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Jōzankei Railway Line|ja|定山渓鉄道線|12=draft}}, the name survives in the bridge over the Okabarushi River on {{ill|National Route 230 (Japan)|ja|国道230号|12=draft}}.{{Sfn|Sapporo City|}}

