: His success led to permission for {{ill|samurai|ja|苗字帯刀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/samurai|qq=}}, and he also served as {{ill|Machi toshiyori|ja|町年寄|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Machi toshiyori|qq=}} and {{ill|Machi bugyō|ja|町奉行|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Machi bugyō|qq=}} assistant, becoming a key figure in the region.{{Sfn|Itō|2008|p=80}}

: In {{ill|1789|ja|1789th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1789|qq=}} ({{ill|Kansei 1|ja|寛政元年|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei 1|qq=}}), following the {{ill|Kunashir-Menashi Rebellion|ja|クナシリ・メナシの戦い|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunashir-Menashi Rebellion|qq=}}, the Matsumae Domain removed Hidaya Kyūbē from his trade rights in Eastern Ezo and assigned Denbē to oversee relief efforts for the Ainu.{{Sfn|Itō|2008|p=81}}

: In {{ill|1790|ja|1790th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1790|qq=}} ({{ill|Kansei 2|ja|寛政2nd year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei 2|qq=}}), he launched an expedition to develop a trading site in {{ill|Sakhalin|ja|樺太|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakhalin|qq=}}, and by {{ill|1798|ja|1798th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1798|qq=}} ({{ill|Kansei 10|ja|寛政10th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei 10|qq=}}), he was hailed as the "Eastern Yokozuna" alongside {{ill|Kōnoike Zen'emon|ja|鴻池善右衛門|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōnoike Zen'emon|qq=}} in the national wealth Rankings.{{Sfn|Itō|2008|p=82}}

: However, in {{ill|1796|ja|1796th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1796|qq=}} ({{ill|Kansei 8|ja|寛政8th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei 8|qq=}}), he was abruptly removed from his trade rights due to political maneuvering by Osaka merchant Koyama Gonbē.{{Sfn|Itō|2008|p=83}} His fortunes were later restored, and in {{ill|1799|ja|1799th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1799|qq=}} ({{ill|Kansei 11|ja|寛政11th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei 11|qq=}}), the Tokugawa Shogunate made him an official government trade manager in Ezo.{{Sfn|Itō|2008|p=84}}

: In {{ill|1915|ja|1915th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1915|qq=}} ({{ill|Taishō 4|ja|大正4th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taishō 4|qq=}}), he was posthumously awarded the {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位|1=Junior Fifth Rank|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Tajiri|1975|p=39}}

