== Legacy ==
[[File:Marujugo Bridge.JPG|thumb|Marujugo Bridge]]
Murayama Denbē is enshrined as one of the 37 deities at [[:en:Hokkaidō Shrine|Hokkaido Shrine]]'s annex, {{ill|Kaitaku Shrine|ja|開拓神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaitaku Shrine|qq=}}.

The area known as '''Fujinosawa''' in [[:en:Minami-ku, Sapporo|Minami-ku, Sapporo]] was once a logging site operated by the Murayama family. The name "Marujugo" persisted locally due to the branded marks on timber. Although the place name faded after the construction of {{ill|Fujinosawa Station|ja|藤の沢駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujinosawa Station|qq=}} on the {{ill|Jōzankei Railway Line|ja|定山渓鉄道線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōzankei Railway Line|qq=}}, the name survives in the bridge over the Okabarushi River on [[:en:Japan National Route 230|National Route 230 (Japan)]].{{Sfn|Sapporo City|}}

