== Legacy ==
[[File:Marujugo Bridge.JPG|thumb|Marujugo Bridge]]
Murayama Denbē is enshrined as one of the 37 deities at {{ill|Hokkaidō Shrine|en|Hokkaidō Shrine|qid=Q710826|lt=Hokkaido Shrine|1=Hokkaidō Shrine}}'s annex, {{ill|Kaitaku Shrine|ja|開拓神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaitaku Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

The area known as '''Fujinosawa''' in {{ill|Minami-ku, Sapporo|en|Minami-ku, Sapporo|qid=Q1134027|lt=Minami-ku, Sapporo|1=Minami-ku, Sapporo}} was once a logging site operated by the Murayama family. The name "Marujugo" persisted locally due to the branded marks on timber. Although the place name faded after the construction of {{ill|Fujinosawa Station|ja|藤の沢駅|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujinosawa Station|1=Fujinosawa Station|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11622624}} on the {{ill|Jōzankei Railway Line|ja|定山渓鉄道線|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōzankei Railway Line|1=Jōzankei Railway Line|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11452195}}, the name survives in the bridge over the Okabarushi River on {{ill|Japan National Route 230|en|Japan National Route 230|qid=Q11421425|lt=National Route 230 (Japan)|1=Japan National Route 230}}.{{Sfn|Sapporo City|}}

